  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.8.0-unstable\r\nOS & Version: OSX Sierra\r\nCommit hash : 722bac84fa503199b9c485c1a3e2bfba03bc487d\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nI send an eth_subscribe to geth.ipc and become subscribed\r\n\r\n$ echo '{\"id\": 1, \"method\": \"eth_subscribe\", \"params\": [\"logs\", {\"topics\": []}]}' | nc -U ~/Library/Ethereum/geth.ipc \r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"result\":\"0xaf428952bdbb919acef8cf35ca9df676\"}\r\n...\r\n...\r\n...more output as txs get processed...\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nConnection closed\r\n\r\n$ echo '{\"id\": 1, \"method\": \"eth_subscribe\", \"params\": [\"logs\", {\"topics\": []}]}' | nc -U ~/Library/Ethereum/geth.ipc \r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"result\":\"0xaf428952bdbb919acef8cf35ca9df676\"}\r\n$ \r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n$ geth --rpc &\r\n$ echo '{\"id\": 1, \"method\": \"eth_subscribe\", \"params\": [\"logs\", {\"topics\": []}]}' | nc -U ~/Library/Ethereum/geth.ipc \r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\nShould codec be closed if the request is a valid subscription?  \r\n\r\n````\r\nfunc (s *Server) ServeCodec(codec ServerCodec, options CodecOption) {\r\n\tdefer codec.Close()\r\n\ts.serveRequest(codec, false, options)\r\n}\r\n\r\n(called from Node.startIPC)\r\n````\r\n\r\n",
